{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}} {{about|the North Korean publisher|similarly-named Soviet publisher|Foreign Languages Publishing House (Soviet Union)}} {{for|the similarly-named publisher in China|Foreign Languages Press}} {{Infobox Korean name | hangul =외국문출판사 | hanja =外國文出版社 | rr =Oegungmun-chulpansa | mr =Oegungmun-ch'ulp'ansa | koreanipa = | context =north | image =Foreign Languages Publishing House.png | caption = }}
The '''Foreign Languages Publishing House''' ('''FLPH''') is the central [[North Korea]]n publishing bureau of foreign-language documents, located in the [[Potonggang-guyok]] of [[Pyongyang]], North Korea.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://geocommons.com/overlays/13207.atom | title=Government Offices, North Korea Uncovered | accessdate=29 October 2013}}</ref> It employs a small group of foreigners to revise translations of North Korean texts so as to make those texts suitable for foreign-language publication.
The publishing house is under the control of the [[Propaganda and Agitation Department]] of the [[Workers' Party of Korea]], which also makes decisions concerning its staff.<ref name=PAD>{{Cite web | title = KWP Propaganda and Agitation Department | work = North Korea Leadership Watch | date = November 2009 | accessdate = 27 May 2018 | url = https://nkleadershipwatch.files.wordpress.com/2009/11/kwppropagandaandagitationdepartment.pdf#page=2 | page = 2}}</ref>
Foreign Languages Publishing House maintains the [[Naenara]] and [[Publications of the DPRK]] web portals,<ref>{{Cite web | title = Naenara | date = 2017 | accessdate = 16 May 2017 | url = http://www.naenara.com.kp/en/ | publisher = Foreign Languages Publishing House }}</ref><ref name="kore_Publ">{{Cite web | title = Publications of the DPRK | accessdate = 16 March 2018 | url = http://www.korean-books.com.kp/en/ | publisher = Foreign Languages Publishing House }}</ref> and publishes the periodicals ''{{ill|Korea (magazine)|ko|조선 (잡지)|lt=Korea}}'', ''[[Korea Today]]'', ''[[Foreign Trade of the DPRK]]'', and the newspaper ''[[Pyongyang Times]]''.<ref name=PAD/>
Foreign Languages Publishing House has a sports team in the [[Paektusan Prize civil servants games]].<ref name="naen_TheP">{{Cite web | title = Paektusan Prize civil servants games continue | author = Ri Sung-ik | work = The Pyongyang Times | date = 9 February 2017 | accessdate = 16 May 2017 | url = http://www.naenara.com.kp/en/order/pytimes/?page=Sports&no=23680 }}</ref>
